From 1bfea2919fc9cecabb9833063570006a01b15bfc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jon Toohill <jtoohill@google.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Apr 2026 21:02:08 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Patch simd-adler32 to enable NEON on 32-bit ARM.

This enables 'stdarch_arm_neon_intrinsics' which is required for
compilation on ARM.

Upstream PR: https://github.com/mcountryman/simd-adler32/pull/31

Note: This patch should be removed once the upstream PR is merged
and a new version of the crate is rolled in Chromium.

Change-Id: Idb8ff71c3ac5cf43e249e4713a3f60fd54bfd403
---
 .../rust/chromium_crates_io/vendor/simd-adler32-v0_3/src/lib.rs  | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/third_party/rust/chromium_crates_io/vendor/simd-adler32-v0_3/src/lib.rs b/third_party/rust/chromium_crates_io/vendor/simd-adler32-v0_3/src/lib.rs
index d65638160a1f7..2254c884eea44 100644
--- a/third_party/rust/chromium_crates_io/vendor/simd-adler32-v0_3/src/lib.rs
+++ b/third_party/rust/chromium_crates_io/vendor/simd-adler32-v0_3/src/lib.rs
@@ -77,6 +77,7 @@
 //!
 //! Feature detection tries to use the fastest supported feature first.
 #![cfg_attr(not(feature = "std"), no_std)]
+#![cfg_attr(target_arch = "arm", feature(stdarch_arm_neon_intrinsics))]
 #![cfg_attr(
   all(feature = "nightly", any(target_arch = "x86", target_arch = "x86_64")),
   feature(stdarch_x86_avx512, avx512_target_feature)
-- 
